Title: ENTERPRISE SOLUTIONS, INC. - Updated October 2024 - 20 Reviews - 2855 Kifer Rd, Santa Clara, California - Employment Agencies - Phone Number - Yelp
Description:
20 reviews of ENTERPRISE SOLUTIONS, INC. "I received three calls within a few hours from the same recruiter. How attentive.

The first suggestion that I update my resume to include a line to show suitability for a particular bullet point in the job description was great. What was less amusing was his insistence that I specifically include that I'm in the San Diego area even though all that's on my resume's header is name, cell and email address.

Playing hypothetical, I asked if the client seeking to hire a 9-month contractor would fly me down after discovering that I'm not in the area. This question was less than skillfully dodged. Then he said that I really should put that I'm in San Diego to avoid being screened out by the client. I pretended to be OK with this and then said I'd send a resume later, which I intended to send WITHOUT adding the false statement that I'm in San Diego. I got the third call an hour after the second call asking where my resume was. I said I planned to get to it in a few hours when not preoccupied with that thing called work but then he got impatient and said that he's concerned it will be too late to do it on Monday since the weekend is approaching and the client needs someone ASAP.

Overall, it sounded like this particular recruiter was the one who needed a resume ASAP, not so much the client. I'm hopeful that others working at this Chicago-based place aren't so sloppy but I'm confident that this particular one must be on the way out or below quota (or other) to have acted as he did.

I fully intend not to followup at all. Sketchy!"
